You can also see a somewhat similar compilation error on Rust Playground [here](https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=nightly&mode=debug&edition=2018&gist=b7143007ecb6190ca675d0112f83a99f).

### Code

I tried this code:

```rust
#![feature(associated_type_bounds, const_generics)]
#![allow(incomplete_features)]

trait Foo {
    type Output;

    fn foo() -> Self::Output;
}

impl Foo for [u8; 3] {
    type Output = [u8; 1 + 2];

    fn foo() -> [u8; 3] {
        [1u8; 3]
    }
}

fn bug<const N: usize>()
where [u8; N]: Foo<Output: AsRef<[u8]>> {
    <[u8; N]>::foo().as_ref();
}

fn main() {
    bug::<3>();
}
```

